                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine and careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>Early 18th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the ruler, the commissioner and other individuals; a few lines (alternating with black lines) and one group of lines in the incipit page of each section of the text; two initial lines of the first commemorative notice of the day and one initial line of the subsequent commemorative notices of the day; the word salām opening the salām-hymns; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements.</seg>
