                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#35vb">ff. 35vb-36</locus>rc: Tarik za-täṣǝḥfä ba-mawāʿǝlihomu la-näguśä nagaśt Yoḥannǝs..., "History that was written in the time of the King of Kings Yoḥannǝs...", a short historiographic composition. <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note, in a mediocre hand, was written during the time of King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. 1872-89), nǝbura ʾǝd ʾIyasu and <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName> Takla Hāymānot and <roleName type="title">ʾalaqā</roleName> Takla ʾƎsṭifānos from Gondär (the scribe?) "who was with them". The note is a list of metropolitans of the Ethiopian Orthodox Church from <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName> salāma to <roleName type="title">ʾabuna</roleName> ʾAtnatewos (in tenure 1867-76), with description of some events. It contains 107 names. Besides, it mentions some rulers of Ethiopia and events that took place when they were in power, such as King Susǝnyos and the arrival of the Catholic priests, the restoration of the Orthodox faith, the rule of King ʾIyasu, the conflict between <roleName type="title">daǧǧāzmāč</roleName> Wube and <roleName type="title">rās</roleName> ʿAli, the death of ʾAtnatewos at ʿAdwa.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#181rb">f. 181rb</locus>-rc: Extensive donation note.<quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in the main hand. It states that the commissioner of the Ms. is <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName> Gǝrma Ṣǝyon who donated it to the Dabra Dāmmo monastery.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">-	The title ስንክሳር and the internal number of the monastic library (384) are written on <locus target="1r">1r</locus>. &#xD;
-	Four lines of the incipit of the Synaxarion are written four times on <locus target="2r">2r</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
